parts.text:
Now I need to implement the proper Game of Life algorithm. Let me write a minimal implementation that passes all 5 active tests.

The algorithm:
1. Build a set of live cells for fast lookup
2. Build a map of neighbor counts for all cells (live + dead neighbors)
3. For each cell with neighbors: apply rules
   - Live cell with 2 neighbors → survives
   - Live cell with 3 neighbors → survives
   - Dead cell with 3 neighbors → born
   - Otherwise → dead

Let me implement:

```typescript
export function nextGeneration(cells: Cell[]): Cell[] {
  if (cells.length === 0) return [];

  const liveSet = new Set(cells.map(([x, y]) => `${x},${y}`));
  const neighborCounts = new Map<string, number>();

  for (const [cx, cy] of cells) {
    for (let dx = -1; dx <= 1; dx++) {
      for (let dy = -1; dy <= 1; dy++) {
        if (dx === 0 && dy === 0) continue;
